1
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:14,167
<i> Bro, hurry!</i>

2
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:17,700
<i> What? Can you still manage?</i>

3
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:18,433
<i> It's okay.</i>

4
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:19,400
<i> You're now accepted.</i>

5
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:20,500
<i> Bobby, you're so petty!</i>

6
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,600
<i>Just because you lost the race,</i>

7
00:00:21,733 --> 00:00:22,833
<i>you messed up my things
to get back at me.</i>

8
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> Do you think I'll accept</i>

9
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,500
<i>that I'm the only one
you threw the shake with?</i>

10
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,800
<i> There you go, I threw it!</i>

11
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:29,800
<i> I'll go to you.</i>

12
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> Let's see each other tomorrow.</i>

13
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,700
<i>Yes, don't worry.
I still have some.</i>

14
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:34,000
<i> That's from boss.</i>

15
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:36,700
<i>But he said,
when you escape from here,</i>

16
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,567
<i> you have to work for him.</i>

17
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,500
<i>I just have one thing
to cross off my list.</i>

18
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:41,533
<i> It's Conde.</i>

19
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,033
<i> Very good.</i>

20
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,300
<i> And because of that,</i>

21
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:47,133
<i>I'll give you everything
you need for your transfer.</i>

22
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,867
<i> Well, they don't know Bobby.</i>

23
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,133
<i>Besides, Bobby doesn't fall
for just anyone.</i>

24
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:52,400
<i> I know someone.</i>

25
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:54,900
<i>I'm sure Bobby won't answer
that one.</i>

26
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:55,700
<i> Who?</i>

27
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,733
<i>The one who isn't courting her.</i>

28
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,400
<i>It's not that she doesn't
want to be courted,</i>

29
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:01,167
<i> she already likes someone.</i>

30
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,233
<i> None other than...</i>

31
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:04,167
<i> Bobby!</i>

32
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:15,133
Sir, what are you doing here?

33
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:19,100
I came from your place.

34
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:21,967
Captain Isang said
that you're here.

35
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:23,233
By the way, this is for you.

36
00:01:24,633 --> 00:01:26,667
I ordered this from Abi.

37
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:31,900
Also, congratulations
on your promotion.

38
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:35,233
Thank you, Sir.

39
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,967
This is delicious.

40
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,600
That's my favorite, turon.

41
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:45,867
Stupid, that's lumpia!

42
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,633
Let's go!

43
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:48,067
Let's eat!

44
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:48,867
Let's go!

45
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,533
Wait...

46
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:50,500
We can't hear anything.

47
00:01:50,633 --> 00:01:51,567
Good bye!

48
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:56,400
Sit down, Sir.

49
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:08,600
Hey, you...

50
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,133
so much is happening
in your life,

51
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:14,200
and you don't even tell me.

52
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:20,333
Is mayor really your father?

53
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,233
How did that happen?

54
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:29,100
Sir, I'm sorry, I don't want
to talk about it.

55
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,200
Sir, how's your
undercover agents

56
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,000
in the Calabari State
University?

57
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,233
They just got in yesterday.

58
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:46,533
I hope they can get some
information there.

59
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,900
Perfect timing.
Vince is video calling.

60
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,667
For sure, he'll give an update.

61
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,967
I'll introduce you.

62
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,167
Okay.

63
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,733
Boss Tonyo, good evening.

64
00:03:07,867 --> 00:03:08,933
Hey, Vince.

65
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:10,200
What's up, how are you?

66
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,300
I'm here at your house.

67
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:15,767
I saw your girlfriend here,
almost naked.

68
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,767
She thought you were the one
coming.

69
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,733
No, Vince. Vince.

70
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:20,600
Tonyo?

71
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:21,833
Hey, Sir Tonyo!

72
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:23,533
What time are you coming home?

73
00:03:23,667 --> 00:03:25,967
Do you want something to eat
so I can cook for you?

74
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:28,333
Or before you come home,

75
00:03:28,467 --> 00:03:30,967
I'll heat up some hot water
so you can take a hot shower.

76
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,000
Or if you want,
after your hot shower,

77
00:03:33,133 --> 00:03:35,167
I'll give you a massage.
I'm good at giving massages.

78
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:38,533
Vince, I'll just call you later.
Just call later.

79
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:39,600
Bye!

80
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:44,767
It's Vince.

81
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,933
Looks like Selena hasn't
moved out yet, Sir.

82
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:54,900
Maybe you should go home
to your girlfriend,

83
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:56,267
who's almost naked.

84
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,067
It's not like that. She's not...

85
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:01,133
Well, I need to go home too,
Sir.

86
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:04,033
Grandmother's not feeling well.
I'll go ahead.

87
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:51,133
Hello, Vince?

88
00:04:51,267 --> 00:04:55,600
For your information,
Selena is not my girlfriend.

89
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:58,600
She's just living there
temporarily! What's with you?

90
00:04:58,733 --> 00:05:00,833
What's with you, Boss?
It's like you don't know me.

91
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,533
Your secret's safe with me.
It's okay, just tell me.

92
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:04,667
Come on.

93
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,467
What? What do you mean
by secret's safe with you?

94
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,200
You're crazy. I'm looking
for a place for her to stay.

95
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,200
Wait...

96
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:14,067
Do you know somewhere
she can stay?

97
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:18,067
Even just a room for rent.

98
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,633
Yes, Boss, I know a place.

99
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:21,000
If you want,
I can come with you.

100
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:23,833
Good. Let's meet later.

101
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:25,700
Bring Selana too.

102
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:28,800
Okay, Boss. I'll message you
the address.

103
00:05:37,167 --> 00:05:41,100
So, Apple, Peach, please
take care of Selena, okay?

104
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:44,400
I think the three of you
will get along.

105
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:45,833
Of course, Tonyo.

106
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:48,900
If they're your friends, then
they're our friends as well.

107
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:53,600
Sir Tonyo, one month advance,
one month deposit.

108
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:57,533
Wait.

109
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:02,667
Here.

110
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,267
Just give it to your landlady.

111
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,000
Okay.

112
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:07,900
Okay...

113
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:10,367
Thank you so much, Sir Tonyo.

114
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:14,600
What now? You won't have anyone
to cook for you anymore.

115
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:17,000
Don't worry, I can handle that.

116
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,600
Okay, I'll just visit you.

117
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:22,767
Your house is just near
this place.

118
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:25,200
Okay. Just be careful here,
okay?

119
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,400
Vince...

120
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:32,167
thank you for helping me
find a place for Selena to stay.

121
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,100
Just keep me updated.

122
00:06:35,233 --> 00:06:36,133
Yes, Boss.

123
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:37,233
Don't mention it.

124
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:46,033
This morning, several persons
deprived of liberty

125
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,433
or PDL will be transferred
to the newly built

126
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:51,833
San Isidro Prison Facility
in Batangas.

127
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:54,500
According to the Calabari
State Prison management,

128
00:06:54,633 --> 00:06:57,600
those selected are models
of change

129
00:06:57,733 --> 00:07:00,800
who deserve to be given
a better environment

130
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:03,367
so that they can further
develop themselves.

131
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:09,767
Sir...

132
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,200
it seems nice to be
a jail guard, right?

133
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:15,233
You can help in the
rehabilitation of PDLs.

134
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,900
How long does it take to train
to become a jail officer?

135
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:22,233
Why? Do you plan to become
a jail guard?

136
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:25,967
I'm thinking about it.

137
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,700
What's with you, Enriquez?

138
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:30,600
You're only thinking
about useless things.

139
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:35,100
What we should be talking
about are meaningful things,

140
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:37,367
important things...

141
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:38,367
like this.

142
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:44,067
Why are women ghosting men?

143
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:47,967
You're talking about
Doc Cecilia, Sir?

144
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:49,467
She has a boyfriend.

145
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,100
Oh, come on. I haven't
answered her yet.

146
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:54,067
It's Vice Mayor Glen Guerrero.

147
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:57,633
Come on.

148
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:03,367
Bobby, can you please move on?

149
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,300
I don't want to play
this game anymore.

150
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:08,500
We've talked about this,
haven't we?

151
00:08:08,633 --> 00:08:11,833
Okay, Sir, if you want,
ask Doc Cecilia.

152
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,267
Shall I call her?

153
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,967
Go ahead, so she can tell you
the truth

154
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,867
because it's hard
if you're being led on.

155
00:08:24,033 --> 00:08:25,467
Okay, okay.

156
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:28,400
I'll confront her now.

157
00:08:28,533 --> 00:08:30,533
I'll call her.
I'll talk to her.

158
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:48,633
Bobby...

159
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,933
Did you know Selena is no longer
staying at my house?

160
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,667
She doesn't live there anymore.

161
00:08:57,367 --> 00:08:58,133
Okay.

162
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:00,933
Bobby, can we talk?

163
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:04,433
About what, Sir?

164
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:06,700
About what happened.

165
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:08,867
What happened?

166
00:09:12,033 --> 00:09:13,067
The...

167
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:15,900
Remember?

168
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,267
Conde...

169
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:22,700
what are you doing?

170
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,000
My nails are just dirty, Chief.

171
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,100
I forgot to cut them.

172
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:31,767
What's up, Sir?

173
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:33,433
I'm going to assign you
some work.

174
00:09:33,567 --> 00:09:35,467
Please go to my office,
you and Garcia.

175
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,267
Yes, Sir.

176
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,567
Enriquez,

177
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:41,133
add some police officers to the
event at Village Tabang-Lupa.

178
00:09:41,267 --> 00:09:42,267
Yes, Sir.

179
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,200
Okay.

180
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:53,033
Sorry, Enriquez...

181
00:09:54,133 --> 00:09:55,333
if we always get interrupted.

182
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,200
Which one, Sir?

183
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,600
- The...
- Enriquez...

184
00:10:04,267 --> 00:10:06,600
I tried to talk to her, but...

185
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:08,933
it seemed like nothing.

186
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:10,533
I can't contact her.

187
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:12,133
Oh no, Sir.

188
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:14,133
That only means one thing...

189
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:16,067
don't be so insensitive.

190
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,700
If she doesn't want
to talk to you,

191
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,633
then she doesn't want
to talk to you.

192
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,400
No, no.

193
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:27,933
Maybe she's just busy
or confused.

194
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,233
I'll still try to talk to her.

195
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,633
You're being transferred
to San Isidro, Batangas.

196
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:48,500
It's spacious and neat there.

197
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:51,200
Be good there.

198
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:54,200
Mando...

199
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:58,500
it's under the chair.

200
00:10:58,633 --> 00:10:59,567
Go ahead.

201
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:02,500
You should go.

202
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:18,433
Bok, is Mandong Warak among
those being transferred?

203
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,633
Looks like he's really changed.

204
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:23,733
Most likely, he must have
watched Green Bones.

205
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:24,967
That has a great story.

206
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:27,000
Maybe.

207
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:29,567
Last time I saw him,
he even saved Gomez.

208
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:30,733
But, Bok...

209
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:34,333
I saw firsthand
how he killed the policemen.

210
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:38,000
He didn't even apologize
to their families.

211
00:11:39,267 --> 00:11:41,067
That's why it's hard to imagine

212
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,367
that someone like him
could change.

213
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:45,233
At least, he'll be transferred.

214
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:47,533
We're safer here
in Calabari now.

215
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,800
And speaking of transferring,

216
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:55,400
Enriquez has plans to transfer
to Calabari Prison.

217
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:57,000
What?

218
00:11:58,367 --> 00:12:00,200
Enriquez wants to transfer?

219
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,400
Is she serious about it?

220
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,133
I don't know.

221
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:07,867
She just mentioned to me
that she wants to be part

222
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,667
of the rehabilitation
of the prisoners.

223
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:13,633
I know.

224
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:17,200
I think she also watched
Green Bones.

225
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:19,033
That show is really good.

226
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:20,233
Have you watched it?

227
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,867
A lot of people say that the
lead character looks like me.

228
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,667
Romel! Romel!

229
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,833
Sir, Romel is having
a heart attack!

230
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:09,067
- Sir, help him!
- Help him!

231
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,567
Dude...

232
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,933
Faye and her friends are doing
a group project now.

233
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:15,633
They need someone to interview.
I said we'll follow, okay?

234
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:19,933
Vince, can we focus
on Jako first?

235
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,700
You can try to be cute
next time.

236
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:24,400
Bro, I've already sent her
a message.

237
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:25,467
Vince, we can't.

238
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:28,533
We need to follow Jako.

239
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,400
Let's go.

240
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:55,867
Bok!

241
00:13:57,367 --> 00:13:59,333
Doc Cecilia texted me.

242
00:14:00,633 --> 00:14:02,000
What did she say?

243
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,400
Wait a minute...

244
00:14:03,533 --> 00:14:04,667
Why did she delete it?

245
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:09,467
I know this kind of style.

246
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:14,167
This is the style of women
who don't answer your calls,

247
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:17,000
pretend to have sent
a wrong message,

248
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:19,367
then they will give you
the address where she is.

249
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,633
These kinds of women
want to be chased, Bok.

250
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,467
I know this very well.

251
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,000
Bok, maybe it was just
sent by mistake.

252
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:28,233
Come on, let's go to where
the chief is telling us to go.

253
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,033
Bok, Bok...

254
00:14:33,167 --> 00:14:36,667
it seems like you really don't
know anything about women.

255
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:40,533
These types are just trying
to be hard to get.

256
00:14:40,667 --> 00:14:44,600
They want me to go to them.
That's it!

257
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:48,700
Who else would mistakenly send
the restaurant's address,

258
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:49,567
which just happens
to be near here?

259
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:50,367
The one over there.

260
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:53,433
Just walking distance.

261
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:55,467
She knows that I'm just
around the area.

262
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,400
She wants me to go to her.

263
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:58,567
Why don't we do this instead?

264
00:14:58,700 --> 00:14:59,800
Just wait for me here.

265
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:01,700
We'll get to work after this.
This will be quick.

266
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:02,867
I'll just go to her.

267
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,567
She's playing hard to get.

268
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,900
Hurry up!

269
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:06,733
Yes!

270
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,167
Hold it!

271
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,633
Hurry!

272
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:07,800
Come on! Let's go!

273
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:19,300
Thank you.

274
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,000
Doc Cecilia!

275
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:24,000
Eric.

276
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:27,233
What are you doing here?

277
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:28,067
What's with you?

278
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,133
Why aren't you answering
my calls?

279
00:16:30,267 --> 00:16:32,200
You want me to miss you so much.

280
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,433
Can we talk?

281
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:38,367
Can we talk at the hospital
some other time?

282
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,833
Let's just talk here, Doc.
It'll just be quick.

283
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:45,633
Well, Bobby mentioned to me
that you have a boyfriend.

284
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:47,800
Well, I know Bobby.

285
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:50,200
She's still bitter
about her love life.

286
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,867
She hasn't moved on from me yet.

287
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,467
But that's not true, right?

288
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,567
You don't have a boyfriend,
right?

289
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:03,567
Yes, it's true that Doc Cecilia
has a boyfriend.

290
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:04,333
It's me.

291
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:13,500
Glen, this is my friend,
Lieutenant Eric Garcia.

292
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:16,733
- This is Vice Mayor Glen.
- Yes, yes, of course.

293
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,933
We've met, haven't we?

294
00:17:19,067 --> 00:17:19,667
Yes, Sir.

295
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,600
Do you come here often?

296
00:17:20,733 --> 00:17:22,467
Can you recommend anything?

297
00:17:24,933 --> 00:17:25,733
Recommend?

298
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:26,733
Yes, yes.

299
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:31,833
I'd recommend not getting
your hopes up.

300
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:35,667
It hurts.

301
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:40,433
Okay, Sir, I'll go ahead.

302
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,467
Okay.

303
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:52,067
Glen, can we just eat?

304
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,167
Relax.

305
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:19,000
Go ahead and escape!
I'll take care of this!

306
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,933
Bok, are you okay? Why...

307
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:58,067
Why do you look like that?

308
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,333
You look like
you've been rejected.

309
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:03,333
Bok...

310
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,767
I thought I wouldn't get hurt
this time.

311
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:12,267
I didn't really think that...

312
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:16,333
I'd get hurt so much.

313
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:26,000
I'm more handsome than
the vice mayor, right?

314
00:19:29,467 --> 00:19:32,167
The vice mayor is Doc Cecilia's
boyfriend?

315
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,067
The message wasn't really
for you.

316
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:42,733
It's your fault, too.
You assumed too much.

317
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:45,033
Bok...

318
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:47,533
how can you do that?

319
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:53,133
I've already been hurt
and you're adding to it.

320
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:54,933
My heart is already bleeding,

321
00:19:55,067 --> 00:19:56,733
yet you're still pouring salt
on it.

322
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,867
Are you happy with that?

323
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,600
Hurting people?

324
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:09,533
It's not like that, Bok,
and that's not true.

325
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,700
I never hurt anyone.

326
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:22,533
Mister!

327
00:20:22,667 --> 00:20:23,500
Can I ask you something?

328
00:20:24,633 --> 00:20:25,667
What is it?

329
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,833
Where's the way
out of the forest?

330
00:20:27,967 --> 00:20:29,400
Just go straight.

331
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:31,633
Wait...

332
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:33,433
Are you a fugitive?

333
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:34,700
Is it obvious?

334
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,567
Give me that machete.
I'm going to need it.

335
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:40,867
Okay.

336
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,500
Just don't kill me.
Please have mercy on me.

337
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:44,933
Don't hurt me.

338
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,367
- Please.
- Yeah, sure.

339
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,433
- Have mercy on me!
- Of course.

340
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:54,533
Hey...

341
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:57,100
Sorry, Mister.

342
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:58,400
I don't need that anymore.

343
00:21:02,033 --> 00:21:03,400
Hey...

344
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,633
Cecilia, look at this.

345
00:21:16,767 --> 00:21:17,633
It's on the news.

346
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:22,300
The Calabari inmates who were
transferred to a new facility...

347
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:23,467
escaped.

348
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,433
It's so ironic

349
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:29,400
because they were transferred
for good behavior,

350
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:31,200
and now, they're hijacking
the bus.

351
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:41,067
You know, I heard one of those
inmates was Mandong Warak.

352
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,767
He's very notorious
for killing policemen.

353
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:46,233
Well...

354
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:49,800
good luck to Garcia
if he escapes.

355
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:52,467
Maybe he'll follow suit.

356
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,600
Please, I already
turned him down.

357
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,233
Don't pick on him.

358
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:00,467
No, no, no.

359
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:02,333
I won't do anything.

360
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:05,767
Unless...

361
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,200
you'll do something first.

362
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,900
Whatever, Glen.

363
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,333
<i> Attention all units.</i>

364
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:29,633
<i>Calabari prisoners escaped into
the Calabari Forest Reserve.</i>

365
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:30,900
<i> We need backup.</i>

366
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:32,267
<i> We need backup.</i>

367
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,500
<i> Prisoners are very dangerous.</i>

368
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:36,733
Alpha, this is Sergeant
Bobby Enriquez.

369
00:22:36,867 --> 00:22:38,967
I'm responding.
I'm near the location.

370
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:44,933
Enriquez is responding alone?

371
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:47,233
Come on, let's go!

372
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:48,767
Isn't that far?

373
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:51,433
I know a shortcut.

374
00:22:57,867 --> 00:23:00,333
The PDL models are being
transferred

375
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:02,267
from Calabari State Prison

376
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,533
to the state-of-the-art facility
in Batangas.

377
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,500
Cut, Faye.

378
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,233
Your face looks oily,
doesn't it?

379
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:09,133
And your pimples are so visible,
girl.

380
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:12,300
We just wanted to ask you
about the money given to you.

381
00:23:12,433 --> 00:23:14,367
Faye!

382
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,233
Help!

383
00:23:16,367 --> 00:23:17,700
Robbers! Help!

384
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:19,500
What are you saying?
You're the bad guy here!

385
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:21,133
You think you can steal this
from me?

386
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:22,567
I'm faster than you!

387
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:25,333
Perfect timing! I'm going to use
my new weapon.
